26 aprif
Londen Jan Kent
Son the 16 curt remitted you £300:- inclosed £475:- t mon
in 4 bills as on the fort of this for which procure the needfull &
advise mee, if be will & accepted as also if ambros apton be
am amble man for there a £500:- him now have before mee
yours of 31 past as to the spa clothes ordered the 2 car must be observed
the imllosed instruction, you have haveinge the patt, because I doubt the
blew cullours will not yo ou fme cloth, lett each convoj carry, or bring a spack
spa clothes that comes for holland & all, or the rest when that for ostend,
butt god knowes when wee shall have one for ostend, onles an english: you do vere
ill not to tollow order, whij not to N8 sent with the king as I have forseen & writt
you so long before, & all a long said, when a convoy presents for amst Rott of
ostend & you have order for spa clothes make a pack, though butt 5 a 6 p & this I
said to often that I am weary to writte & yett you will not do itt, I exspected
M N8 4: a 5 blew grayes as Iordered & you send one p. you never was so
negligent with mee as this time. of warr, onles itt be you will please others better
the ships from hull are att amst. well arrived as also scot & the other roth. strisp
now wee must staye for the next convoy, to have the rest of my order from thence com
pleated, I ordered to send severall sorts of pennestons, to see which walleld
sall best & you send all of one prixe so that you follow more your minde
